config: setup Tailwind CSS and postcss configuration :-

Step-by-steps :-

1. Install Tailwind CSS

Run this in your project:

npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
npx tailwindcss init -p

2. Configure tailwind.config.js

/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
export default {
  content: [
    "./index.html",
    "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}",
  ],
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}

3. Update index.css (or src/index.css)

Remove everything and add:

@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;

4. Clean App.jsx for Testing Tailwind
function App() {
  return (
    <div className="flex items-center justify-center h-screen bg-gray-100">
      <h1 className="text-4xl font-bold text-blue-600">
        StudyMate 🚀 Tailwind Working
      </h1>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;

5. Run Project :- 

npm run dev


